Role: QA Lead/ sr.QA Automation Tester  
 
The Identity and Access Management (IAM) Program will introduce a new global Identity Management capability for all 
of  Zurich.  The  capabilities  include  a  new  global  unique  username,  a  unified  access  and  account  request  application,  a

Client: BMW, Germany, NJ                                                                                                                 Dec 13 – Feb 17 
Role: QA Lead 
 
Projects: 
 
PSYTEKK:  
Psytekk is a PEP related planning system. The shortening of the PEP process is one of the basic targets of BMW Group; 
here the tooling process of press parts is time critical. The central process is the local planning of the technical parts 
manufacturing concept. Here, all data and structures relevant for project consideration and project follow up in the 
planning process (for example- Pressing, Tool set, work sequence, Plate section, Coiling, Test equipment, Container, etc. 
) are created and maintained.  
RW/BV:

planning process (for example- Pressing, Tool set, work sequence, Plate section, Coiling, Test equipment, Container, etc. 
) are created and maintained.  
RW/BV: 
RW/BV is SAO Applications for BMW, here we have created different modes of shopping carts using SRM and performing 
functional tests for end-to-end business flows and data integration between SRM, CAI, TUQ, PortalM, and RWQ Systems. 
 
EAI-Migration: 
BMW  EAI  Migration  is  the  migration  of  middleware  technology  from  Oracle  See  beyond  to  IBM  WebSphere  Message 
Broker.  As  part  of  this  project,  flows  are  tested  from  Message  Queues/flat  files/Database  to  SAP  Inbound/Outbound 
interfaces. Testing involves triggering IDOCs for SAP Outbound interfaces and test the data transformations in Message 
queues,  flat  files  and  databases.  For  SAP  inbound  interfaces,  triggering  messages  at  Message  Broker  tool  with  flat

queues,  flat  files  and  databases.  For  SAP  inbound  interfaces,  triggering  messages  at  Message  Broker  tool  with  flat 
files/message queues and then validate the data transformation in SAP Inbound IDOCs. 
 
CARMEN: 
CARMEN  integrates  its  dealer  front  end  (RFE)  into  the  BMW  dealer  system  landscape  via  S-Gate  /  SiteMinder  internet 
integration. It stores the dealer information, and the vehicle information like who is the owner, user and other details. 
 
Environment: Selenium WebDriver, SOAP UI, Jenkins, SAP SRM, CRM, SD, SCM, Load Runner , TESTNG, XPath, Eclipse, IBM 
WebSphere,  HTML,  Firepath,  Firebug,  CSS,  HP  Quality  Center,  MS- Office  (Excel,  Word),  Agile  Scrum,  SQL,  Oracle  and 
Windows.

Role: QA Engineer 
 
Dr Reddy's foundation is a CSR Project (Corporate Social responsibility). It was a privilege to  work on this project. What

Role: QA Engineer 
 
Dr Reddy's foundation is a CSR Project (Corporate Social responsibility). It was a privilege to  work on this project. What 
DRF does is, it encourages lower and below lower class children to join into their institutions for a minimal fee and allows 
them   to learn   courses   on   day   to   day   jobs.   Thereafter   conducts   recruitment   drives  by   tying   up   with  multiple

organizations. The  main  aim  of  this  Web  application  is  to  provide  a  login/register  page  for  end  users.  Also  there  are 
business user logins (Project Manager, HR, Center Head, etc.) who needs to approve the requests at multiple levels, track 
the attendance, recruit the staff, and do the payments. 
 
Environment: Manual Testing,  HP Quality Canter, Oracle, Java, JavaScript, VBScript, HTML, SSL, Windows, UNIX, SQL 
server, IE.
